KEITH: Yeah. It's kind of remarkable. Past debates, the speaking time has been really divergent. And in this one, the - these four people - and then if you add Biden in it, it's pretty close.
KURTZLEBEN: Oh, yeah.
KHALID: I mean, you have four candidates who all spoke within a minute of one another in terms of their length. And to me, this was one of the strengths of having a debate where you only had seven candidates. I say only because some of the candidates probably still think that's too many. But the point was...
KEITH: (Laughter)
